column149: participantComments:"I don't think yellow would be upset that purple went closer in the final round because purple's decision does not detract from yellow's harvest. the fact that the harvest for one was independent of the other's actions
column150: plus the fact that purple changed course in the last round suggested they did not have an unspoken agreement. If they lost berries because of the other's decisions
column151: I think they would be more likely to create an agreement. Good luck with your study!"
